"""
intelligence/engine.py — Production market-intelligence engine v3
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Five-pillar conviction scoring with DYNAMIC WEIGHTING, async parallel
fetching, disk-backed TTL caching, and graceful API degradation.

PILLARS & BASE WEIGHTS
──────────────────────
  Pillar  Base Wt  Source
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  sent     20 %   StockTwits  (public stream, no key needed)
  ins      20 %   FMP v4  /api/v4/insider-trading
  inst     20 %   FMP v3  /api/v3/institutional-holder/{sym}
  news     20 %   Finnhub /api/v1/company-news  + VADER NLP
  macro    20 %   Finnhub /api/v1/stock/recommendation

DYNAMIC WEIGHTING RULES  (calculate_dynamic_weights)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  1. High Conviction : CEO/C-suite purchase > $1M  → boost ins to 40%
  2. Momentum        : StockTwits volume > 2σ      → boost sent
  3. Data Availability: missing pillar → redistribute weight to active ones

CONFIDENCE LEVEL
────────────────
  100% = 5/5 pillars with real data
   40% = 2/5 pillars with real data
  Tracked per-fetch via has_data flag in pillar metadata.

CACHE TTLs  macro=4h  ins=24h  inst=24h  news=15min  sent=5min

BACKWARD COMPATIBILITY
──────────────────────
  get_advanced_score(symbol) → Tuple[Signal, IntelligenceScore]  (unchanged)
  IntelligenceScore legacy field mapping:
    flow_score      = inst score
    congress_score  = news score
    sentiment_score = sent score
"""

